ance to bend the curve,=E2=80=9D Wall Street argot for trying to make thing=
s happen the way you=E2=80=99d like them to happen. <br/><br/>The key, Marc=
 explained in the meeting, was that the economy had responded positively si=
nce the election and that everything that Trump wanted to do with his agend=
a could happen against the =E2=80=9Cwindfall=E2=80=9D from =E2=80=9Cregulat=
ory relaxation,=E2=80=9D the =E2=80=9Cenergy expansion,=E2=80=9D and the ge=
neral =E2=80=9Cbrightening of the mood=E2=80=9D of the country. He urged Tr=
ump to make sure to =E2=80=9Cpay attention=E2=80=9D to inflation and intere=
st rates because elections and mandates are
won and lost largely on those two economic touchstones. It was a very easy,=
 =E2=80=9Crelaxed=E2=80=9D conversation. (Someone even described it as =E2=
